    {
      "id": "8fb740ebb271b131b05501e33e2ae9698d1db9e4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-04 06:17:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(6 inline comments)\n\nSome defects in the patch that need to be fixed.\n\nI'm reluctant to land this before it does anything useful, and especially if resize2fs crashes the system, or otherwise breaks things, because with the previous behaviour it was at least clearly not working and relatively safe.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "35ef0d7c54d60f5ffd329eed23303f8adae1b8f2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-04 06:35:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nAh, I didn't notice the second part of your posting in LU-137 because it was hidden in a scrolling window.  It looks like you got SETVERSION, SETFLAGS, and resize2fs to work, which is great.\n\nIn that case, please change the sanity.sh test to positively verify that the ioctl passthrough is working:\n\n         do_facet mds$i chattr +T /mnt/mds$i ||\n                 error \"chattr +T /mnt/mds$i failed\"\n         do_facet mds$i lsattr -d /mnt/mds$i | grep -- -T[-e] ||\n                 error \"lsattr /mnt/mds$i missing 'T'\"\n         do_facet mds$i chattr -T /mnt/mds$i ||\n                 error \"chattr +T /mnt/mds$i failed\"\n\n\nand add a conf-sanity test that does some online resizing, similar to what you described in your Jira comment.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "161a2e2be7ee32ad5164200ba28a3316064ad2f4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 360,
        "name": "Swapnil Pimpale",
        "email": "pimpale.swapnil@gmail.com",
        "username": "spimpale"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-04 11:10:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nchattr and lsattr won't work on server mountpoints without modifications to e2fsprogs.\nIf used on server mountpoints today they throw this error\n\"Not a directory while trying to stat /mnt/mds1/\"\n\nPlease advise if modifying e2fsprogs is the way we would like to go.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "db55fa9b1aaacc176d560cca481e49b514bc2ad3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-09-25 05:39:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nCould you please clarify why lsattr/chattr do not work on the Lustre mountpoint?  Looking at the code it appears they are doing the obvious thing:\n\n        fd = open (name, OPEN_FLAGS);\n        r = ioctl(fd, EXT2_IOC_GETFLAGS, &f);\nor\n        r = ioctl(fd, EXT2_IOC_SETFLAGS, &f);\n\nlike your test program is.  The only difference I can see is that stat() is called on the device beforehand.  Maybe we need to add a basic \"getattr\" method for the mountpoint?\n\nIn any case, lsattr/chattr are only intended as a starting point to get the code into basic working order.  The real goal is to get resize2fs to be able to do online resizing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e1a577db74da96afdf5a365532bf02a8d201ab48",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2014-03-04 00:34:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nLooks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
